34 // Evaluate an expression containing condition register ----
35 // or condition register field symbols. Returns positive ----
36 // value on success, or -1 on error. ----
37 static int64_t ----
38 EvaluateCRExpr(const MCExpr *E) { 0
39 switch (E->getKind()) { 0
40 case MCExpr::Target: 0
41 return -1; 0
42 ----
43 case MCExpr::Constant: { 0
44 int64_t Res = cast(E)->getValue(); 0
45 return Res < 0 ? -1 : Res; 0
46 } ----
47 ----
48 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: { 0
49 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = cast(E); 0
50 StringRef Name = SRE->getSymbol().getName(); 0
51 ----
52 if (Name == "lt") return 0; 0
53 if (Name == "gt") return 1; 0
54 if (Name == "eq") return 2; 0
55 if (Name == "so") return 3; 0
56 if (Name == "un") return 3; 0
57 ----
58 if (Name == "cr0") return 0; 0
59 if (Name == "cr1") return 1; 0
60 if (Name == "cr2") return 2; 0
61 if (Name == "cr3") return 3; 0
62 if (Name == "cr4") return 4; 0
63 if (Name == "cr5") return 5; 0
64 if (Name == "cr6") return 6; 0
65 if (Name == "cr7") return 7; 0
66 ----
67 return -1; 0
68 } ----
69 ----
70 case MCExpr::Unary: 0
71 return -1; 0
72 ----
73 case MCExpr::Binary: { 0
74 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(E); 0
75 int64_t LHSVal = EvaluateCRExpr(BE->getLHS()); 0
76 int64_t RHSVal = EvaluateCRExpr(BE->getRHS()); 0
77 int64_t Res; ----
78 ----
79 if (LHSVal < 0 || RHSVal < 0) 0
80 return -1; 0
81 ----
82 switch (BE->getOpcode()) { 0
83 default: return -1; 0
84 case MCBinaryExpr::Add: Res = LHSVal + RHSVal; break; 0
85 case MCBinaryExpr::Mul: Res = LHSVal * RHSVal; break; 0
86 } ----
87 ----
88 return Res < 0 ? -1 : Res; 0
89 } ----
90 } ----
91 ----
92 llvm_unreachable("Invalid expression kind!"); 0
93 } ----

167 /// PPCOperand - Instances of this class represent a parsed PowerPC machine ----

169 struct PPCOperand : public MCParsedAsmOperand { ----
170 enum KindTy { ----
171 Token, ----
172 Immediate, ----
173 ContextImmediate, ----
174 Expression, ----
175 TLSRegister ----
176 } Kind; ----
177 ----
178 SMLoc StartLoc, EndLoc; ----
179 bool IsPPC64; ----
180 ----
181 struct TokOp { ----
182 const char *Data; ----
183 unsigned Length; ----
184 }; ----
185 ----
186 struct ImmOp { ----
187 int64_t Val; ----
188 }; ----
189 ----
190 struct ExprOp { ----
191 const MCExpr *Val; ----
192 int64_t CRVal; // Cached result of EvaluateCRExpr(Val) ----
193 }; ----
194 ----
195 struct TLSRegOp { ----
196 const MCSymbolRefExpr *Sym; ----
197 }; ----
198 ----
199 union { ----
200 struct TokOp Tok; ----
201 struct ImmOp Imm; ----
202 struct ExprOp Expr; ----
203 struct TLSRegOp TLSReg; ----
204 }; ----
205 ----
206 PPCOperand(KindTy K) : Kind(K) {} 0
207 ----
208 public: ----
209 PPCOperand(const PPCOperand &o) : MCParsedAsmOperand() { ----
210 Kind = o.Kind; ----
211 StartLoc = o.StartLoc; ----
212 EndLoc = o.EndLoc; ----
213 IsPPC64 = o.IsPPC64; ----
214 switch (Kind) { ----
215 case Token: ----
216 Tok = o.Tok; ----
217 break; ----
218 case Immediate: ----
219 case ContextImmediate: ----
220 Imm = o.Imm; ----
221 break; ----
222 case Expression: ----
223 Expr = o.Expr; ----
224 break; ----
225 case TLSRegister: ----
226 TLSReg = o.TLSReg; ----
227 break; ----
228 } ----
229 } ----

392 } ----

394 bool isTLSReg() const { return Kind == TLSRegister; } 0
395 bool isDirectBr() const { 0
396 if (Kind == Expression) 0
397 return true; 0
398 if (Kind != Immediate) 0
399 return false; 0
400 // Operand must be 64-bit aligned, signed 27-bit immediate. ----
401 if ((getImm() & 3) != 0) 0
402 return false; 0
403 if (isInt<26>(getImm())) 0
404 return true; 0
405 if (!IsPPC64) { 0
406 // In 32-bit mode, large 32-bit quantities wrap around. ----
407 if (isUInt<32>(getImm()) && isInt<26>(static_cast(getImm()))) 0
408 return true; 0
409 } ----
410 return false; 0
411 } ----

618 void addS16ImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
619 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
620 switch (Kind) { 0
621 case Immediate: 0
622 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(getImm())); 0
623 break; 0
624 case ContextImmediate: 0
625 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(getImmS16Context())); 0
626 break; 0
627 default: 0
628 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(getExpr())); 0
629 break; 0
630 } ----
631 } 0
632 ----
633 void addU16ImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
634 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
635 switch (Kind) { 0
636 case Immediate: 0
637 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(getImm())); 0
638 break; 0
639 case ContextImmediate: 0
640 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(getImmU16Context())); 0
641 break; 0
642 default: 0
643 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(getExpr())); 0
644 break; 0
645 } ----
646 } 0
647 ----
648 void addBranchTargetOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
649 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
650 if (Kind == Immediate) 0
651 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(getImm() / 4)); 0
652 else ----
653 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(getExpr())); 0
654 } 0
655 ----
656 void addTLSRegOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
657 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
658 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(getTLSReg())); 0
659 } 0
660 ----
661 StringRef getToken() const { 0
662 assert(Kind == Token && "Invalid access!"); 0
663 return StringRef(Tok.Data, Tok.Length); 0
664 } ----
665 ----
666 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const override; ----
667 ----
668 static std::unique_ptr CreateToken(StringRef Str, SMLoc S, 0
669 bool IsPPC64) { ----
670 auto Op = std::make_unique(Token); 0
671 Op->Tok.Data = Str.data(); 0
672 Op->Tok.Length = Str.size(); 0
673 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
674 Op->EndLoc = S; 0
675 Op->IsPPC64 = IsPPC64; 0
676 return Op; 0
677 } ----
678 ----
679 static std::unique_ptr ----
680 CreateTokenWithStringCopy(StringRef Str, SMLoc S, bool IsPPC64) { 0
681 // Allocate extra memory for the string and copy it. ----
682 // FIXME: This is incorrect, Operands are owned by unique_ptr with a default ----
683 // deleter which will destroy them by simply using "delete", not correctly ----
684 // calling operator delete on this extra memory after calling the dtor ----
685 // explicitly. ----
686 void *Mem = ::operator new(sizeof(PPCOperand) + Str.size()); 0
687 std::unique_ptr Op(new (Mem) PPCOperand(Token)); 0
688 Op->Tok.Data = reinterpret_cast(Op.get() + 1); 0
689 Op->Tok.Length = Str.size(); 0
690 std::memcpy(const_cast(Op->Tok.Data), Str.data(), Str.size()); 0
691 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
692 Op->EndLoc = S; 0
693 Op->IsPPC64 = IsPPC64; 0
694 return Op; 0
695 } ----
696 ----
697 static std::unique_ptr CreateImm(int64_t Val, SMLoc S, SMLoc E, 0
698 bool IsPPC64) { ----
699 auto Op = std::make_unique(Immediate); 0
700 Op->Imm.Val = Val; 0
701 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
702 Op->EndLoc = E; 0
703 Op->IsPPC64 = IsPPC64; 0
704 return Op; 0
705 } ----
706 ----
707 static std::unique_ptr CreateExpr(const MCExpr *Val, SMLoc S, 0
708 SMLoc E, bool IsPPC64) { ----
709 auto Op = std::make_unique(Expression); 0
710 Op->Expr.Val = Val; 0
711 Op->Expr.CRVal = EvaluateCRExpr(Val); 0
712 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
713 Op->EndLoc = E; 0
714 Op->IsPPC64 = IsPPC64; 0
715 return Op; 0
716 } ----
717 ----
718 static std::unique_ptr ----
719 CreateTLSReg(const MCSymbolRefExpr *Sym, SMLoc S, SMLoc E, bool IsPPC64) { 0
720 auto Op = std::make_unique(TLSRegister); 0
721 Op->TLSReg.Sym = Sym; 0
722 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
723 Op->EndLoc = E; 0
724 Op->IsPPC64 = IsPPC64; 0
725 return Op; 0
726 } ----
727 ----
728 static std::unique_ptr ----
729 CreateContextImm(int64_t Val, SMLoc S, SMLoc E, bool IsPPC64) { 0
730 auto Op = std::make_unique(ContextImmediate); 0
731 Op->Imm.Val = Val; 0
732 Op->StartLoc = S; 0
733 Op->EndLoc = E; 0
734 Op->IsPPC64 = IsPPC64; 0
735 return Op; 0
736 } ----
737 ----
738 static std::unique_ptr ----
739 CreateFromMCExpr(const MCExpr *Val, SMLoc S, SMLoc E, bool IsPPC64) { 0
740 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(Val)) 0
741 return CreateImm(CE->getValue(), S, E, IsPPC64); 0
742 ----
743 if (const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = dyn_cast(Val)) 0
744 if (SRE->getKind() == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TLS || 0
745 SRE->getKind() == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TLS_PCREL) 0
746 return CreateTLSReg(SRE, S, E, IsPPC64); 0
747 ----
748 if (const PPCMCExpr *TE = dyn_cast(Val)) { 0
749 int64_t Res; ----
750 if (TE->evaluateAsConstant(Res)) 0
751 return CreateContextImm(Res, S, E, IsPPC64); 0
752 } ----
753 ----
754 return CreateExpr(Val, S, E, IsPPC64); 0
755 } ----
756 ----
757 private: ----
758 template ----
759 bool isExtImm(bool Signed, unsigned Multiple) const { 0
760 switch (Kind) { 0
761 default: 0
762 return false; 0
763 case Expression: 0
764 return true; 0
765 case Immediate: 0
766 case ContextImmediate: ----
767 if (Signed) 0
768 return isInt(getImmS16Context()) && 0
769 (getImmS16Context() & (Multiple - 1)) == 0; 0
770 else ----
771 return isUInt(getImmU16Context()) && 0
772 (getImmU16Context() & (Multiple - 1)) == 0; 0
773 } ----
774 } ----
775 }; ----
776 ----
777 } // end anonymous namespace. ----
778 ----
779 void PPCOperand::print(raw_ostream &OS) const { 0
780 switch (Kind) { 0
781 case Token: 0
782 OS << "'" << getToken() << "'"; 0
783 break; 0
784 case Immediate: 0
785 case ContextImmediate: ----
786 OS << getImm(); 0
787 break; 0
788 case Expression: 0
789 OS << *getExpr(); 0
790 break; 0
791 case TLSRegister: 0
792 OS << *getTLSReg(); 0
793 break; 0
794 } ----
795 } 0
796 ----
797 static void ----
798 addNegOperand(MCInst &Inst, MCOperand &Op, MCContext &Ctx) { 0
799 if (Op.isImm()) { 0
800 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(-Op.getImm())); 0
801 return; 0
802 } ----
803 const MCExpr *Expr = Op.getExpr(); 0
804 if (const MCUnaryExpr *UnExpr = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
805 if (UnExpr->getOpcode() == MCUnaryExpr::Minus) { 0
806 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(UnExpr->getSubExpr())); 0
807 return; 0
808 } ----
809 } else if (const MCBinaryExpr *BinExpr = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
810 if (BinExpr->getOpcode() == MCBinaryExpr::Sub) { 0
811 const MCExpr *NE = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(BinExpr->getRHS(), 0
812 BinExpr->getLHS(), Ctx); ----
813 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(NE)); 0
814 return; 0
815 } ----
816 } ----
817 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(MCUnaryExpr::createMinus(Expr, Ctx))); 0
818 } ----
819 ----
820 void PPCAsmParser::ProcessInstruction(MCInst &Inst, 0
821 const OperandVector &Operands) { ----
822 int Opcode = Inst.getOpcode(); 0
823 switch (Opcode) { 0
824 case PPC::DCBTx: 0
825 case PPC::DCBTT: ----
826 case PPC::DCBTSTx: ----
827 case PPC::DCBTSTT: { ----
828 MCInst TmpInst; 0
829 TmpInst.setOpcode((Opcode == PPC::DCBTx || Opcode == PPC::DCBTT) ? 0
830 PPC::DCBT : PPC::DCBTST); ----
831 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm( 0
832 (Opcode == PPC::DCBTx || Opcode == PPC::DCBTSTx) ? 0 : 16)); 0
833 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
834 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
835 Inst = TmpInst; 0
836 break; 0
837 } 0
838 case PPC::DCBTCT: 0
839 case PPC::DCBTDS: { ----
840 MCInst TmpInst; 0
841 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::DCBT); 0
842 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); 0
843 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
844 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
845 Inst = TmpInst; 0
846 break; 0
847 } 0
848 case PPC::DCBTSTCT: 0
849 case PPC::DCBTSTDS: { ----
850 MCInst TmpInst; 0
851 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::DCBTST); 0
852 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); 0
853 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
854 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
855 Inst = TmpInst; 0
856 break; 0
857 } 0
858 case PPC::DCBFx: 0
859 case PPC::DCBFL: ----
860 case PPC::DCBFLP: ----
861 case PPC::DCBFPS: ----
862 case PPC::DCBSTPS: { ----
863 int L = 0; 0
864 if (Opcode == PPC::DCBFL) 0
865 L = 1; 0
866 else if (Opcode == PPC::DCBFLP) 0
867 L = 3; 0
868 else if (Opcode == PPC::DCBFPS) 0
869 L = 4; 0
870 else if (Opcode == PPC::DCBSTPS) 0
871 L = 6; 0
872 ----
873 MCInst TmpInst; 0
874 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::DCBF); 0
875 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(L)); 0
876 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
877 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
878 Inst = TmpInst; 0
879 break; 0
880 } 0
881 case PPC::LAx: { 0
882 MCInst TmpInst; 0
883 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::LA); 0
884 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
885 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); 0
886 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
887 Inst = TmpInst; 0
888 break; 0
889 } 0
890 case PPC::SUBI: { 0
891 MCInst TmpInst; 0
892 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDI); 0
893 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
894 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
895 addNegOperand(TmpInst, Inst.getOperand(2), getContext()); 0
896 Inst = TmpInst; 0
897 break; 0
898 } 0
899 case PPC::SUBIS: { 0
900 MCInst TmpInst; 0
901 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDIS); 0
902 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
903 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
904 addNegOperand(TmpInst, Inst.getOperand(2), getContext()); 0
905 Inst = TmpInst; 0
906 break; 0
907 } 0
908 case PPC::SUBIC: { 0
909 MCInst TmpInst; 0
910 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDIC); 0
911 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
912 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
913 addNegOperand(TmpInst, Inst.getOperand(2), getContext()); 0
914 Inst = TmpInst; 0
915 break; 0
916 } 0
917 case PPC::SUBIC_rec: { 0
918 MCInst TmpInst; 0
919 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDIC_rec); 0
920 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
921 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
922 addNegOperand(TmpInst, Inst.getOperand(2), getContext()); 0
923 Inst = TmpInst; 0
924 break; 0
925 } 0
926 case PPC::EXTLWI: 0
927 case PPC::EXTLWI_rec: { ----
928 MCInst TmpInst; 0
929 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
930 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
931 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::EXTLWI ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
932 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
933 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
934 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B)); 0
935 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
936 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N - 1)); 0
937 Inst = TmpInst; 0
938 break; 0
939 } 0
940 case PPC::EXTRWI: 0
941 case PPC::EXTRWI_rec: { ----
942 MCInst TmpInst; 0
943 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
944 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
945 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::EXTRWI ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
946 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
947 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
948 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B + N)); 0
949 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(32 - N)); 0
950 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(31)); 0
951 Inst = TmpInst; 0
952 break; 0
953 } 0
954 case PPC::INSLWI: 0
955 case PPC::INSLWI_rec: { ----
956 MCInst TmpInst; 0
957 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
958 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
959 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::INSLWI ? PPC::RLWIMI : PPC::RLWIMI_rec); 0
960 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
961 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
962 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
963 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(32 - B)); 0
964 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B)); 0
965 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm((B + N) - 1)); 0
966 Inst = TmpInst; 0
967 break; 0
968 } 0
969 case PPC::INSRWI: 0
970 case PPC::INSRWI_rec: { ----
971 MCInst TmpInst; 0
972 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
973 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
974 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::INSRWI ? PPC::RLWIMI : PPC::RLWIMI_rec); 0
975 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
976 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
977 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
978 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(32 - (B + N))); 0
979 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B)); 0
980 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm((B + N) - 1)); 0
981 Inst = TmpInst; 0
982 break; 0
983 } 0
984 case PPC::ROTRWI: 0
985 case PPC::ROTRWI_rec: { ----
986 MCInst TmpInst; 0
987 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
988 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::ROTRWI ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
989 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
990 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
991 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(32 - N)); 0
992 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
993 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(31)); 0
994 Inst = TmpInst; 0
995 break; 0
996 } 0
997 case PPC::SLWI: 0
998 case PPC::SLWI_rec: { ----
999 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1000 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1001 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::SLWI ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
1002 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1003 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1004 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N)); 0
1005 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1006 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(31 - N)); 0
1007 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1008 break; 0
1009 } 0
1010 case PPC::SRWI: 0
1011 case PPC::SRWI_rec: { ----
1012 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1013 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1014 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::SRWI ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
1015 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1016 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1017 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(32 - N)); 0
1018 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N)); 0
1019 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(31)); 0
1020 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1021 break; 0
1022 } 0
1023 case PPC::CLRRWI: 0
1024 case PPC::CLRRWI_rec: { ----
1025 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1026 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1027 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::CLRRWI ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
1028 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1029 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1030 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1031 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1032 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(31 - N)); 0
1033 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1034 break; 0
1035 } 0
1036 case PPC::CLRLSLWI: 0
1037 case PPC::CLRLSLWI_rec: { ----
1038 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1039 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1040 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1041 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::CLRLSLWI ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
1042 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1043 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1044 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N)); 0
1045 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B - N)); 0
1046 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(31 - N)); 0
1047 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1048 break; 0
1049 } 0
1050 case PPC::EXTLDI: 0
1051 case PPC::EXTLDI_rec: { ----
1052 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1053 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1054 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1055 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::EXTLDI ? PPC::RLDICR : PPC::RLDICR_rec); 0
1056 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1057 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1058 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B)); 0
1059 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N - 1)); 0
1060 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1061 break; 0
1062 } 0
1063 case PPC::EXTRDI: 0
1064 case PPC::EXTRDI_rec: { ----
1065 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1066 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1067 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1068 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::EXTRDI ? PPC::RLDICL : PPC::RLDICL_rec); 0
1069 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1070 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1071 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B + N)); 0
1072 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(64 - N)); 0
1073 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1074 break; 0
1075 } 0
1076 case PPC::INSRDI: 0
1077 case PPC::INSRDI_rec: { ----
1078 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1079 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1080 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1081 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::INSRDI ? PPC::RLDIMI : PPC::RLDIMI_rec); 0
1082 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1083 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1084 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1085 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(64 - (B + N))); 0
1086 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B)); 0
1087 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1088 break; 0
1089 } 0
1090 case PPC::ROTRDI: 0
1091 case PPC::ROTRDI_rec: { ----
1092 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1093 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1094 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::ROTRDI ? PPC::RLDICL : PPC::RLDICL_rec); 0
1095 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1096 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1097 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(64 - N)); 0
1098 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1099 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1100 break; 0
1101 } 0
1102 case PPC::SLDI: 0
1103 case PPC::SLDI_rec: { ----
1104 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1105 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1106 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::SLDI ? PPC::RLDICR : PPC::RLDICR_rec); 0
1107 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1108 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1109 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N)); 0
1110 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(63 - N)); 0
1111 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1112 break; 0
1113 } 0
1114 case PPC::SUBPCIS: { 0
1115 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1116 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1117 TmpInst.setOpcode(PPC::ADDPCIS); 0
1118 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1119 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(-N)); 0
1120 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1121 break; 0
1122 } 0
1123 case PPC::SRDI: 0
1124 case PPC::SRDI_rec: { ----
1125 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1126 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1127 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::SRDI ? PPC::RLDICL : PPC::RLDICL_rec); 0
1128 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1129 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1130 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(64 - N)); 0
1131 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N)); 0
1132 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1133 break; 0
1134 } 0
1135 case PPC::CLRRDI: 0
1136 case PPC::CLRRDI_rec: { ----
1137 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1138 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1139 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::CLRRDI ? PPC::RLDICR : PPC::RLDICR_rec); 0
1140 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1141 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1142 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1143 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(63 - N)); 0
1144 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1145 break; 0
1146 } 0
1147 case PPC::CLRLSLDI: 0
1148 case PPC::CLRLSLDI_rec: { ----
1149 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1150 int64_t B = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1151 int64_t N = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1152 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::CLRLSLDI ? PPC::RLDIC : PPC::RLDIC_rec); 0
1153 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1154 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1155 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(N)); 0
1156 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B - N)); 0
1157 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1158 break; 0
1159 } 0
1160 case PPC::RLWINMbm: 0
1161 case PPC::RLWINMbm_rec: { ----
1162 unsigned MB, ME; ----
1163 int64_t BM = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1164 if (!isRunOfOnes(BM, MB, ME)) 0
1165 break; 0
1166 ----
1167 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1168 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::RLWINMbm ? PPC::RLWINM : PPC::RLWINM_rec); 0
1169 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1170 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1171 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); 0
1172 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(MB)); 0
1173 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ME)); 0
1174 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1175 break; 0
1176 } 0
1177 case PPC::RLWIMIbm: 0
1178 case PPC::RLWIMIbm_rec: { ----
1179 unsigned MB, ME; ----
1180 int64_t BM = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1181 if (!isRunOfOnes(BM, MB, ME)) 0
1182 break; 0
1183 ----
1184 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1185 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::RLWIMIbm ? PPC::RLWIMI : PPC::RLWIMI_rec); 0
1186 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1187 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // The tied operand. 0
1188 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1189 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); 0
1190 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(MB)); 0
1191 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ME)); 0
1192 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1193 break; 0
1194 } 0
1195 case PPC::RLWNMbm: 0
1196 case PPC::RLWNMbm_rec: { ----
1197 unsigned MB, ME; ----
1198 int64_t BM = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1199 if (!isRunOfOnes(BM, MB, ME)) 0
1200 break; 0
1201 ----
1202 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1203 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode == PPC::RLWNMbm ? PPC::RLWNM : PPC::RLWNM_rec); 0
1204 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); 0
1205 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); 0
1206 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); 0
1207 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(MB)); 0
1208 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ME)); 0
1209 Inst = TmpInst; 0
1210 break; 0
1211 } 0
1212 case PPC::MFTB: { 0
1213 if (getSTI().hasFeature(PPC::FeatureMFTB)) { 0
1214 assert(Inst.getNumOperands() == 2 && "Expecting two operands"); 0
1215 Inst.setOpcode(PPC::MFSPR); 0
1216 } ----
1217 break; 0
1218 } ----
1219 } ----
1220 } 0
1221 ----
1222 static std::string PPCMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS, ----
1223 unsigned VariantID = 0); ----
1224 ----
1225 bool PPCAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode, 0
1226 OperandVector &Operands, ----
1227 MCStreamer &Out, uint64_t &ErrorInfo, ----
1228 bool MatchingInlineAsm) { ----
1229 MCInst Inst; 0
1230 ----
1231 switch (MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, ErrorInfo, MatchingInlineAsm)) { 0
1232 case Match_Success: 0
1233 // Post-process instructions (typically extended mnemonics) ----
1234 ProcessInstruction(Inst, Operands); 0
1235 Inst.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
1236 Out.emitInstruction(Inst, getSTI()); 0
1237 return false; 0
1238 case Match_MissingFeature: 0
1239 return Error(IDLoc, "instruction use requires an option to be enabled"); 0
1240 case Match_MnemonicFail: { 0
1241 FeatureBitset FBS = ComputeAvailableFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits()); 0
1242 std::string Suggestion = PPCMnemonicSpellCheck( ----
1243 ((PPCOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken(), FBS); 0
1244 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction" + Suggestion, 0
1245 ((PPCOperand &)*Operands[0]).getLocRange()); 0
1246 } 0
1247 case Match_InvalidOperand: { 0
1248 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
1249 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL) { 0
1250 if (ErrorInfo >= Operands.size()) 0
1251 return Error(IDLoc, "too few operands for instruction"); 0
1252 ----
1253 ErrorLoc = ((PPCOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1254 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc()) ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
1255 } ----
1256 ----
1257 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction"); 0
1258 } ----
1259 } ----
1260 ----
1261 llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!"); 0
1262 } 0
1263 ----
1264 bool PPCAsmParser::MatchRegisterName(MCRegister &RegNo, int64_t &IntVal) { 0
1265 if (getParser().getTok().is(AsmToken::Percent)) 0
1266 getParser().Lex(); // Eat the '%'. 0
1267 ----
1268 if (!getParser().getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
1269 return true; 0
1270 ----
1271 StringRef Name = getParser().getTok().getString(); 0
1272 if (Name.equals_insensitive("lr")) { 0
1273 RegNo = isPPC64() ? PPC::LR8 : PPC::LR; 0
1274 IntVal = 8; 0
1275 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("ctr")) { 0
1276 RegNo = isPPC64() ? PPC::CTR8 : PPC::CTR; 0
1277 IntVal = 9; 0
1278 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("vrsave")) { 0
1279 RegNo = PPC::VRSAVE; 0
1280 IntVal = 256; 0
1281 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("r") && 0
1282 !Name.substr(1).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 32) { 0
1283 RegNo = isPPC64() ? XRegs[IntVal] : RRegs[IntVal]; 0
1284 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("f") && 0
1285 !Name.substr(1).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 32) { 0
1286 RegNo = FRegs[IntVal]; 0
1287 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("vs") && 0
1288 !Name.substr(2).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 64) { 0
1289 RegNo = VSRegs[IntVal]; 0
1290 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("v") && 0
1291 !Name.substr(1).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 32) { 0
1292 RegNo = VRegs[IntVal]; 0
1293 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("cr") && 0
1294 !Name.substr(2).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 8) { 0
1295 RegNo = CRRegs[IntVal]; 0
1296 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("acc") && 0
1297 !Name.substr(3).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 8) { 0
1298 RegNo = ACCRegs[IntVal]; 0
1299 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("wacc_hi") && 0
1300 !Name.substr(7).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 8) { 0
1301 RegNo = ACCRegs[IntVal]; 0
1302 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("wacc") && 0
1303 !Name.substr(4).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 8) { 0
1304 RegNo = WACCRegs[IntVal]; 0
1305 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("dmrrowp") && 0
1306 !Name.substr(7).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 32) { 0
1307 RegNo = DMRROWpRegs[IntVal]; 0
1308 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("dmrrow") && 0
1309 !Name.substr(6).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 64) { 0
1310 RegNo = DMRROWRegs[IntVal]; 0
1311 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("dmrp") && 0
1312 !Name.substr(4).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 4) { 0
1313 RegNo = DMRROWpRegs[IntVal]; 0
1314 } else if (Name.starts_with_insensitive("dmr") && 0
1315 !Name.substr(3).getAsInteger(10, IntVal) && IntVal < 8) { 0
1316 RegNo = DMRRegs[IntVal]; 0
1317 } else ----
1318 return true; 0
1319 getParser().Lex(); 0
1320 return false; 0
1321 } ----
1322 ----
1323 bool PPCAsmParser::parseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
1324 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
1325 if (tryParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc) != MatchOperand_Success) 0
1326 return TokError("invalid register name"); 0
1327 return false; 0
1328 } ----
1329 ----
1330 OperandMatchResultTy PPCAsmParser::tryParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, 0
1331 SMLoc &StartLoc, ----
1332 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
1333 const AsmToken &Tok = getParser().getTok(); 0
1334 StartLoc = Tok.getLoc(); 0
1335 EndLoc = Tok.getEndLoc(); 0
1336 RegNo = 0; 0
1337 int64_t IntVal; ----
1338 if (MatchRegisterName(RegNo, IntVal)) 0
1339 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1340 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1341 } ----
1342 ----
1343 /// Extract \code @l/@ha \endcode modifier from expression. Recursively scan ----
1344 /// the expression and check for VK_PPC_LO/HI/HA ----
1345 /// symbol variants. If all symbols with modifier use the same ----
1346 /// variant, return the corresponding PPCMCExpr::VariantKind, ----
1347 /// and a modified expression using the default symbol variant. ----
1348 /// Otherwise, return NULL. ----
1349 const MCExpr *PPCAsmParser:: 0
1350 ExtractModifierFromExpr(const MCExpr *E, ----
1351 PPCMCExpr::VariantKind &Variant) { ----
1352 MCContext &Context = getParser().getContext(); 0
1353 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_None; 0
1354 ----
1355 switch (E->getKind()) { 0
1356 case MCExpr::Target: 0
1357 case MCExpr::Constant: ----
1358 return nullptr; 0
1359 ----
1360 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: { 0
1361 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = cast(E); 0
1362 ----
1363 switch (SRE->getKind()) { 0
1364 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_LO: 0
1365 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_LO; 0
1366 break; 0
1367 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HI: 0
1368 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HI; 0
1369 break; 0
1370 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HA: 0
1371 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HA; 0
1372 break; 0
1373 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HIGH: 0
1374 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HIGH; 0
1375 break; 0
1376 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHA: 0
1377 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHA; 0
1378 break; 0
1379 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHER: 0
1380 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHER; 0
1381 break; 0
1382 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHERA: 0
1383 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHERA; 0
1384 break; 0
1385 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHEST: 0
1386 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHEST; 0
1387 break; 0
1388 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHESTA: 0
1389 Variant = PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_HIGHESTA; 0
1390 break; 0
1391 default: 0
1392 return nullptr; 0
1393 } ----
1394 ----
1395 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(&SRE->getSymbol(), Context); 0
1396 } ----
1397 ----
1398 case MCExpr::Unary: { 0
1399 const MCUnaryExpr *UE = cast(E); 0
1400 const MCExpr *Sub = ExtractModifierFromExpr(UE->getSubExpr(), Variant); 0
1401 if (!Sub) 0
1402 return nullptr; 0
1403 return MCUnaryExpr::create(UE->getOpcode(), Sub, Context); 0
1404 } ----
1405 ----
1406 case MCExpr::Binary: { 0
1407 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(E); 0
1408 PPCMCExpr::VariantKind LHSVariant, RHSVariant; ----
1409 const MCExpr *LHS = ExtractModifierFromExpr(BE->getLHS(), LHSVariant); 0
1410 const MCExpr *RHS = ExtractModifierFromExpr(BE->getRHS(), RHSVariant); 0
1411 ----
1412 if (!LHS && !RHS) 0
1413 return nullptr; 0
1414 ----
1415 if (!LHS) LHS = BE->getLHS(); 0
1416 if (!RHS) RHS = BE->getRHS(); 0
1417 ----
1418 if (LHSVariant == PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_None) 0
1419 Variant = RHSVariant; 0
1420 else if (RHSVariant == PPCMCExpr::VK_PPC_None) 0
1421 Variant = LHSVariant; 0
1422 else if (LHSVariant == RHSVariant) 0
1423 Variant = LHSVariant; 0
1424 else ----
1425 return nullptr; 0
1426 ----
1427 return MCBinaryExpr::create(BE->getOpcode(), LHS, RHS, Context); 0
1428 } ----
1429 } ----
1430 ----
1431 llvm_unreachable("Invalid expression kind!"); 0
1432 } ----
1433 ----
1434 /// Find all VK_TLSGD/VK_TLSLD symbol references in expression and replace ----
1435 /// them by VK_PPC_TLSGD/VK_PPC_TLSLD. This is necessary to avoid having ----
1436 /// _GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE_ created via ELFObjectWriter::RelocNeedsGOT. ----
1437 /// FIXME: This is a hack. ----
1438 const MCExpr *PPCAsmParser:: 0
1439 FixupVariantKind(const MCExpr *E) { ----
1440 MCContext &Context = getParser().getContext(); 0
1441 ----
1442 switch (E->getKind()) { 0
1443 case MCExpr::Target: 0
1444 case MCExpr::Constant: ----
1445 return E; 0
1446 ----
1447 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: { 0
1448 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = cast(E); 0
1449 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None; 0
1450 ----
1451 switch (SRE->getKind()) { 0
1452 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_TLSGD: 0
1453 Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TLSGD; 0
1454 break; 0
1455 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_TLSLD: 0
1456 Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_PPC_TLSLD; 0
1457 break; 0
1458 default: 0
1459 return E; 0
1460 } ----
1461 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(&SRE->getSymbol(), Variant, Context); 0
1462 } ----
1463 ----
1464 case MCExpr::Unary: { 0
1465 const MCUnaryExpr *UE = cast(E); 0
1466 const MCExpr *Sub = FixupVariantKind(UE->getSubExpr()); 0
1467 if (Sub == UE->getSubExpr()) 0
1468 return E; 0
1469 return MCUnaryExpr::create(UE->getOpcode(), Sub, Context); 0
1470 } ----
1471 ----
1472 case MCExpr::Binary: { 0
1473 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(E); 0
1474 const MCExpr *LHS = FixupVariantKind(BE->getLHS()); 0
1475 const MCExpr *RHS = FixupVariantKind(BE->getRHS()); 0
1476 if (LHS == BE->getLHS() && RHS == BE->getRHS()) 0
1477 return E; 0
1478 return MCBinaryExpr::create(BE->getOpcode(), LHS, RHS, Context); 0
1479 } ----
1480 } ----
1481 ----
1482 llvm_unreachable("Invalid expression kind!"); 0
1483 } ----
1484 ----
1485 /// ParseExpression. This differs from the default "parseExpression" in that ----
1486 /// it handles modifiers. ----
1487 bool PPCAsmParser:: 0
1488 ParseExpression(const MCExpr *&EVal) { ----
1489 // (ELF Platforms) ----
1490 // Handle \code @l/@ha \endcode ----
1491 if (getParser().parseExpression(EVal)) 0
1492 return true; 0
1493 ----
1494 EVal = FixupVariantKind(EVal); 0
1495 ----
1496 PPCMCExpr::VariantKind Variant; ----
1497 const MCExpr *E = ExtractModifierFromExpr(EVal, Variant); 0
1498 if (E) 0
1499 EVal = PPCMCExpr::create(Variant, E, getParser().getContext()); 0
1500 ----
1501 return false; 0
1502 } ----
1503 ----
1504 /// ParseOperand ----
1505 /// This handles registers in the form 'NN', '%rNN' for ELF platforms and ----
1506 /// rNN for MachO. ----
1507 bool PPCAsmParser::ParseOperand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1508 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
1509 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1510 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1); 0
1511 const MCExpr *EVal; ----
1512 ----
1513 // Attempt to parse the next token as an immediate ----
1514 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1515 // Special handling for register names. These are interpreted ----
1516 // as immediates corresponding to the register number. ----
1517 case AsmToken::Percent: { 0
1518 MCRegister RegNo; 0
1519 int64_t IntVal; ----
1520 if (MatchRegisterName(RegNo, IntVal)) 0
1521 return Error(S, "invalid register name"); 0
1522 ----
1523 Operands.push_back(PPCOperand::CreateImm(IntVal, S, E, isPPC64())); 0
1524 return false; 0
1525 } ----
1526 case AsmToken::Identifier: 0
1527 case AsmToken::LParen: ----
1528 case AsmToken::Plus: ----
1529 case AsmToken::Minus: ----
1530 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
1531 case AsmToken::Dot: ----
1532 case AsmToken::Dollar: ----
1533 case AsmToken::Exclaim: ----
1534 case AsmToken::Tilde: ----
1535 if (!ParseExpression(EVal)) 0
1536 break; 0
1537 // Fall-through ----
1538 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1539 default: ----
1540 return Error(S, "unknown operand"); 0
1541 } ----
1542 ----
1543 // Push the parsed operand into the list of operands ----
1544 Operands.push_back(PPCOperand::CreateFromMCExpr(EVal, S, E, isPPC64())); 0
1545 ----
1546 // Check whether this is a TLS call expression ----
1547 bool TLSCall = false; 0
1548 if (const MCSymbolRefExpr *Ref = dyn_cast(EVal)) 0
1549 TLSCall = Ref->getSymbol().getName() == "__tls_get_addr"; 0
1550 ----
1551 if (TLSCall && parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::LParen)) { 0
1552 const MCExpr *TLSSym; ----
1553 S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1554 if (ParseExpression(TLSSym)) 0
1555 return Error(S, "invalid TLS call expression"); 0
1556 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected ')'")) 0
1557 return true; 0
1558 E = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1559 ----
1560 Operands.push_back(PPCOperand::CreateFromMCExpr(TLSSym, S, E, isPPC64())); 0
1561 } ----
1562 ----
1563 // Otherwise, check for D-form memory operands ----
1564 if (!TLSCall && parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::LParen)) { 0
1565 S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1566 ----
1567 int64_t IntVal; ----
1568 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1569 case AsmToken::Percent: { 0
1570 MCRegister RegNo; 0
1571 if (MatchRegisterName(RegNo, IntVal)) 0
1572 return Error(S, "invalid register name"); 0
1573 break; 0
1574 } ----
1575 case AsmToken::Integer: 0
1576 if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(IntVal) || IntVal < 0 || 0
1577 IntVal > 31) 0
1578 return Error(S, "invalid register number"); 0
1579 break; 0
1580 case AsmToken::Identifier: 0
1581 default: ----
1582 return Error(S, "invalid memory operand"); 0
1583 } ----
1584 ----
1585 E = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
1586 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RParen, "missing ')'")) 0
1587 return true; 0
1588 Operands.push_back(PPCOperand::CreateImm(IntVal, S, E, isPPC64())); 0
1589 } ----
1590 ----
1591 return false; 0
1592 } ----
1593 ----
1594 /// Parse an instruction mnemonic followed by its operands. ----
1595 bool PPCAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, StringRef Name, 0
1596 SMLoc NameLoc, OperandVector &Operands) { ----
1597 // The first operand is the token for the instruction name. ----
1598 // If the next character is a '+' or '-', we need to add it to the ----
1599 // instruction name, to match what TableGen is doing. ----
1600 std::string NewOpcode; 0
1601 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Plus)) { 0
1602 NewOpcode = std::string(Name); 0
1603 NewOpcode += '+'; 0
1604 Name = NewOpcode; 0
1605 } ----
1606 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Minus)) { 0
1607 NewOpcode = std::string(Name); 0
1608 NewOpcode += '-'; 0
1609 Name = NewOpcode; 0
1610 } ----
1611 // If the instruction ends in a '.', we need to create a separate ----
1612 // token for it, to match what TableGen is doing. ----
1613 size_t Dot = Name.find('.'); 0
1614 StringRef Mnemonic = Name.slice(0, Dot); 0
1615 if (!NewOpcode.empty()) // Underlying memory for Name is volatile. 0
1616 Operands.push_back( 0
1617 PPCOperand::CreateTokenWithStringCopy(Mnemonic, NameLoc, isPPC64())); 0
1618 else ----
1619 Operands.push_back(PPCOperand::CreateToken(Mnemonic, NameLoc, isPPC64())); 0
1620 if (Dot != StringRef::npos) { 0
1621 SMLoc DotLoc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(NameLoc.getPointer() + Dot); 0
1622 StringRef DotStr = Name.slice(Dot, StringRef::npos); 0
1623 if (!NewOpcode.empty()) // Underlying memory for Name is volatile. 0
1624 Operands.push_back( 0
1625 PPCOperand::CreateTokenWithStringCopy(DotStr, DotLoc, isPPC64())); 0
1626 else ----
1627 Operands.push_back(PPCOperand::CreateToken(DotStr, DotLoc, isPPC64())); 0
1628 } ----
1629 ----
1630 // If there are no more operands then finish ----
1631 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) 0
1632 return false; 0
1633 ----
1634 // Parse the first operand ----
1635 if (ParseOperand(Operands)) 0
1636 return true; 0
1637 ----
1638 while (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) { 0
1639 if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma) || ParseOperand(Operands)) 0
1640 return true; 0
1641 } ----
1642 ----
1643 // We'll now deal with an unfortunate special case: the syntax for the dcbt ----
1644 // and dcbtst instructions differs for server vs. embedded cores. ----
1645 // The syntax for dcbt is: ----
1646 // dcbt ra, rb, th [server] ----
1647 // dcbt th, ra, rb [embedded] ----
1648 // where th can be omitted when it is 0. dcbtst is the same. We take the ----
1649 // server form to be the default, so swap the operands if we're parsing for ----
1650 // an embedded core (they'll be swapped again upon printing). ----
1651 if (getSTI().hasFeature(PPC::FeatureBookE) && 0
1652 Operands.size() == 4 && 0
1653 (Name == "dcbt" || Name == "dcbtst")) { 0
1654 std::swap(Operands[1], Operands[3]); 0
1655 std::swap(Operands[2], Operands[1]); 0
1656 } ----
1657 ----
1658 // Handle base mnemonic for atomic loads where the EH bit is zero. ----
1659 if (Name == "lqarx" || Name == "ldarx" || Name == "lwarx" || 0
1660 Name == "lharx" || Name == "lbarx") { 0
1661 if (Operands.size() != 5) 0
1662 return false; 0
1663 PPCOperand &EHOp = (PPCOperand &)*Operands[4]; 0
1664 if (EHOp.isU1Imm() && EHOp.getImm() == 0) 0
1665 Operands.pop_back(); 0
1666 } ----
1667 ----
1668 return false; 0
1669 } 0
1670 ----
1671 /// ParseDirective parses the PPC specific directives ----
1672 bool PPCAsmParser::ParseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) { 0
1673 StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getIdentifier(); 0
1674 if (IDVal == ".word") 0
1675 ParseDirectiveWord(2, DirectiveID); 0
1676 else if (IDVal == ".llong") 0
1677 ParseDirectiveWord(8, DirectiveID); 0
1678 else if (IDVal == ".tc") 0
1679 ParseDirectiveTC(isPPC64() ? 8 : 4, DirectiveID); 0
1680 else if (IDVal == ".machine") 0
1681 ParseDirectiveMachine(DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
1682 else if (IDVal == ".abiversion") 0
1683 ParseDirectiveAbiVersion(DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
1684 else if (IDVal == ".localentry") 0
1685 ParseDirectiveLocalEntry(DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
1686 else if (IDVal.startswith(".gnu_attribute")) 0
1687 ParseGNUAttribute(DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
1688 else ----
1689 return true; 0
1690 return false; 0
1691 } ----
1692 ----
1693 /// ParseDirectiveWord ----
1694 /// ::= .word [ expression (, expression)* ] ----
1695 bool PPCAsmParser::ParseDirectiveWord(unsigned Size, AsmToken ID) { 0
1696 auto parseOp = [&]() -> bool { 0
1697 const MCExpr *Value; ----
1698 SMLoc ExprLoc = getParser().getTok().getLoc(); 0
1699 if (getParser().parseExpression(Value)) 0
1700 return true; 0
1701 if (const auto *MCE = dyn_cast(Value)) { 0
1702 assert(Size <= 8 && "Invalid size"); 0
1703 uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue(); 0
1704 if (!isUIntN(8 * Size, IntValue) && !isIntN(8 * Size, IntValue)) 0
1705 return Error(ExprLoc, "literal value out of range for '" + 0
1706 ID.getIdentifier() + "' directive"); 0
1707 getStreamer().emitIntValue(IntValue, Size); 0
1708 } else ----
1709 getStreamer().emitValue(Value, Size, ExprLoc); 0
1710 return false; 0
1711 }; 0
1712 ----
1713 if (parseMany(parseOp)) 0
1714 return addErrorSuffix(" in '" + ID.getIdentifier() + "' directive"); 0
1715 return false; 0
1716 } ----
1717 ----
1718 /// ParseDirectiveTC ----
1719 /// ::= .tc [ symbol (, expression)* ] ----
1720 bool PPCAsmParser::ParseDirectiveTC(unsigned Size, AsmToken ID) { 0
1721 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
1722 // Skip TC symbol, which is only used with XCOFF. ----
1723 while (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement) 0
1724 && getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) 0
1725 Parser.Lex(); 0
1726 if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma)) 0
1727 return addErrorSuffix(" in '.tc' directive"); 0
1728 ----
1729 // Align to word size. ----
1730 getParser().getStreamer().emitValueToAlignment(Align(Size)); 0
1731 ----
1732 // Emit expressions. ----
1733 return ParseDirectiveWord(Size, ID); 0
1734 } ----
1735 ----
1736 /// ParseDirectiveMachine (ELF platforms) ----
1737 /// ::= .machine [ cpu | "push" | "pop" ] ----
1738 bool PPCAsmParser::ParseDirectiveMachine(SMLoc L) { 0
1739 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
1740 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier) && 0
1741 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String)) 0
1742 return Error(L, "unexpected token in '.machine' directive"); 0
1743 ----
1744 StringRef CPU = Parser.getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
1745 ----
1746 // FIXME: Right now, the parser always allows any available ----
1747 // instruction, so the .machine directive is not useful. ----
1748 // In the wild, any/push/pop/ppc64/altivec/power[4-9] are seen. ----
1749 ----
1750 Parser.Lex(); 0
1751 ----
1752 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) 0
1753 return addErrorSuffix(" in '.machine' directive"); 0
1754 ----
1755 PPCTargetStreamer *TStreamer = static_cast( ----
1756 getParser().getStreamer().getTargetStreamer()); 0
1757 if (TStreamer != nullptr) 0
1758 TStreamer->emitMachine(CPU); 0
1759 ----
1760 return false; 0
1761 } ----

779 void PPCOperand::print(raw_ostream &OS) const { 779 void PPCOperand::print(raw_ostream &OS) const {
780 switch (Kind) { 780 switch (Kind) {
781 case Token: 781 case Token:
782 OS << "'" << getToken() << "'"; 782 OS << "'" << getToken() << "'";
783 break; 783 break;
784 case Immediate: 784 case Immediate:
